<HEADLINE> South Chinese Province Welcomes '97 China Tourism Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 1 (Xinhua) -- This morning at Huangpu Port,
the Guangdong Tourism Bureau welcomed nearly 700 tourists from
western Europe - its first group for 1997.
</P>
<P>
The largest parade in the history of Guangdong's capital,
Guangzhou, was also held this morning, with over 500 people
performing along the streets, while 40 vehicles from Guangzhou
city, Jiangmen city, Australia, the Republic of Korea, Thailand,
the United States, Hong Kong, and Macao attracted hundreds of
thousands of onlookers with their colorful decorations.
</P>
<P>
The Huanggang border check point in Shenzhen city and Gongbei
border check point in Zhuhai also held celebrations for the first
groups of tourists entering China in 1997.
</P>
<P>
At Huanggang, 240 tourists from Europe, the United States,
Japan and the Republic of Korea were presented with fresh flowers,
souvenir badges, and tickets to some scenic spots. Some 70,000 to
80,000 tourists entered China through Shenzhen Customs today.
</P>
<P>
Shantou had a tourism fair today while Shenzhen and Zhaoqing
gave tourist parties tonight to celebrate '97 China Tourism.
</P>
<P>
Gao Siren, secretary of the Guangzhou City Party Committee,
said that various tourist activities will help build bridges of
friendship between people living in Guangzhou, Hong Kong and
Macao, and that Guangzhou will make its own contribution to Hong
Kong's return to the motherland and to the long-term prosperity
and stability of Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
