<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Holds New Year Party </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 1 (Xinhua) -- The Association for
Celebrating Hong Kong's Return to China held a grand cocktail
party here today to celebrate the coming of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Over 1,000 local celebrities including Chief Executive
designate of the future Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(SAR) Tung Chee Hwa attended the party.
</P>
<P>
Tung said when addressing the party that the year 1997 is quite
special, because it marks the beginning of a new era. This is the
time Hong Kong people should celebrate and be happy about.
</P>
<P>
He said there are many things to celebrate in the year: the
great step forward in the country's unification, the prosperity of
the Chinese nation, an even better future for Hong Kong, the
ending of colonial rule in Hong Kong and her return to the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
He also told the press that the organizing of the SAR
government will be carried out step by step on the basis of broad
consultation. In the past few days, he has met with a number of
senior civil servants to seek their advice.
</P>
<P>
"Everything should be carried out in favor of Hong Kong's
smooth transition, this is the most important point," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the Association Henry Fok Ying-tung also delivered
a speech at the party.
</P>
<P>
The association has had 1,500 members and has so far raised a
fund of some 70 million Hong Kong dollars (8.97 million US
dollars). It will organize a series of major activities to
celebrate the handover of Hong Kong.  
</P>
</TEXT>
