<HEADLINE> Zimbabwean Railways Raise Passenger Fares </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, January 1 (Xinhua) -- The National Railways of
Zimbabwe (NRZ) has increased its passenger fares by between
20-40 percent with effect from today to offset ever
increasing running costs.
</P>
<P>
NRZ spokesman Gamaliel Rungani confirmed that the decision to
include bedding charges for first and second class travelers in
the new fares is to make it more convenient for travelers who
currently were required to buy traveling and bedding tickets
separately.
</P>
<P>
But other officials said the bedding facility was being
under-utilised as most travelers opted to bring their own
blankets and the decision to include bedding charges in the new
fares is a way of marketing the facility. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
