<HEADLINE> Namibian President Stresses Need To Ensure Peace, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Namibian President Sam
Nujoma today urged the defense and security forces to work harder
in 1997 to ensure peace and stability in the southern African
country.
</P>
<P>
In his New Year message monitored here today, Nujoma said that
during the past year, Namibia had been blessed with peace and
stability which he said are "scarce commodities" in many African
countries afflicted with violence and conflict.
</P>
<P>
The Namibian president said his government would spare no
efforts to maintain them.
</P>
<P>
Nujoma also stressed the need to eradicate poverty enable poor
children access to education. 
</P>
