<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UK Weathers Coldest New Year's Day for Decades </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Britain weathered one of the
coldest New Year's Days for nearly two decades, which left many
roads impassable, claimed several lives and postponed dozens of
football games.
</P>
<P>
According to the London Weather Center, the windchill factor
brought the temperature in the capital down to -12C on the New
Year's Eve.
</P>
<P>
In London, the chimes of Big Ben, one of its tourist
attractions were silenced for more than two hours when the
mechanism froze Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
More than 70,000 people braved sub-zero temperatures to
celebrate the new year in Trafalgar Square at the center of London
on the New Year's Eve, despite falling snow, an alcohol ban and
police's annual appeal to the public to stay away.
</P>
<P>
Traditionally, Trafalgar Square is the focus of London
celebrations with people there singing, dancing and kissing each
other on the stroke of midnight.
</P>
<P>
Another 20,000 more merrymakers filled the surrounding streets.
They shivered and shook as they celebrated the approaching of the
new year.
</P>
<P>
There were 21 arrests as numbers swelled in the countdown to
1997, mainly for drunk and disorderly behavior, others for
possessing an offensive weapon.
</P>
<P>
Snowfall was close to the records, with nearly five inches near
Eastbourne, East Sussex, the heaviest fall in the south of England
since l981.
</P>
<P>
The windchill factor from Russia was making it feel much
colder, and snow and ice were making driving hazardous in many
areas. North Yorkshire was declared an emergency area as
snowploughs and gritters worked to keep roads open.
</P>
<P>
On the A36 near Bath, a 26-year-old driver from Trowbridge,
Wiltshire, died in a head-on collision thought to have been caused
by ice.
</P>
<P>
In Caversham, near Reading, an elderly woman was killed when
she slipped on an icy pavement, fell into the road and was run
over by a car.
</P>
<P>
In Bristol, a 64-year-old man was killed by a car as he walked
in the road with his wife to avoid slippery pavements.
</P>
<P>
The cold weather ruined the New Year's Day program, with 23
Premiership and Football League games. The icy spell is also
threatening to ruin the weekend's FA Cup games scheduled for
Saturday and Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Temperatures are not expected to rise above a maximum of 0C
(32F) today. Most areas will be colder with the windchill factor
adding to the bleak outlook.
</P>
<P>
A London Weather Center spokeswoman said, "We are likely to see
it very cold with some snow, a few flakes for a lot of people
rather than huge falls." 
</P>
</TEXT>
