<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ugandan President Stresses Peace ,Stability </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri
Museveni today stressed peace and stability in his new year
address to the nation.
</P>
<P>
In his address delivered from his home at Rwakitura,
southwestern Uganda, Museveni said peace and stability are two
basic interests of all the citizens of Uganda.
</P>
<P>
On the issue of security, he called upon all leaders in the
areas of insurgency to educate the people about the real nature
of the insurgency, adding that it is unfortunate that some people
have been tricked into fighting a proxy war, whose objectives and
consequences they do not understand.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated his determination to fulfill the contract he
made with the people of Uganda in his election manifesto last May
on development and modernization.
</P>
<P>
Turning to the regional issues, he regretted the bombing of
Ugandan territory by Sudan, a sign that the Sudanese government is
not serious about peace despite the agreement signed between the
two countries for the settlement of disputes.
</P>
<P>
He said that despite this bad signal from Sudan, Uganda will
continue with the peace process and expressed gratitude to the
governments of Iran, Malawi and Libya for their anticipation in
the peace-making process.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed concern about the situation in Burundi and
Zaire and reiterated Uganda's commitment to the resolutions of
the Arusha summit.
</P>
<P>
He ensured the whole region and those involved in the conflict
that Uganda is not involved in the conflict in Zaire, and that
Uganda's only wish is to see peace and stability re-established in
the whole region so that there can be development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
