<HEADLINE> Northwestern Chinese Province Speeding Up Expressway Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, January 2 (Xinhua) -- A ceremony was held in Xi'an, in
Shaanxi Province, on December 31, 1996, marking the opening of an
expressway from Lintong City to Weinan City and the start of work
on another from Weinan to Tongguan Town.
</P>
<P>
The two sections are the last part of the east-west provincial
expressway project in this inland province.
</P>
<P>
The Weinan-Tongguan section is being built with World Bank
loans and is scheduled to be completed by the end of 1999, at a
total cost of over 1.9 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The new expressway is expected to allow the landlocked province
to join the proposed east-west cross-country highway.  
</P>
</TEXT>
