<HEADLINE> US Pair Reach Hopman Cup Tennis Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Unseeded United States pair
Justin Gimelstob and Chanda Rubin advanced to the final of the
Hopman Cup tennis mixed teams tournament in Perth, Australia
Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
They beat Australia in a crucial tie at Burswood Dome.
</P>
<P>
The Americans are likely to meet South Africa in the final,
though Switzerland and Romania still have a chance of qualifying.
</P>
<P>
Gimelstob, who came to Perth an unknown as a last-minute
replacement for Richey Reneberg, clinched the match for the United
States with a stirring three-sets victory over Mark Philippoussis
7-6 (7/4), 4-6, 7-6 (7-5).
</P>
<P>
His teammate Rubin outclassed Nicole Bradtke 7-5, 6-0 in an
hour.
</P>
<P>
The mixed doubles clash is still to be played, but this will
have no meaningful bearing on the outcome of the tie,
</P>
<P>
France ended the tournament without a win in three ties, having
earlier been beaten 2-1 by the United States and by a similar
margin by Australia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
