<HEADLINE> Shanghai: Tops In China's Film Shows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 2 (Xinhua) -- In 1996, China's largest city
earned 260 million yuan in film ticket sales, up five percent over
the year before, putting it first in the country.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's Daguangming Cinema alone took in some 20 million
yuan, or half of last year's total sales of cinemas in Tianjin,
the third largest city in China.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, nearly 20 films brought in over one million yuan in
Shanghai's cinemas, including 10 Chinese films, which earned over
two million yuan each, according to local officials.
</P>
