<HEADLINE> China Exporting Diesel Locomotives to Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Four diesel locomotives, one of
them named the "General Abacha" after Nigerian President Sani
Abacha, were readied for export to Nigeria today.
</P>
<P>
A ribbon-cutting ceremony was held at the Dalian Rolling Stock
Plant in the coastal city of Dalian, in northeast China's Liaoning
Province. The four Dongfeng-IV locomotives are the first to be
exported to Nigeria, and mark the first time China has exported
electric diesel locomotives to Africa.
</P>
<P>
The Dalian Rolling Stock Plant will produce 16 more diesel
locomotives of the same type for Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
Their top speed is 100 kilometers per hour.
</P>
<P>
The Dalian Rolling Stock Plant previously exported 18
locomotives to Myanmar, the Democratic People's Republic of Korea,
and Nigeria.  
</P>
