<HEADLINE> Steady Prices For Chinese Spring Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 2 (Xinhua) -- The State Council, China's
highest governing body, has issued a circular urging central
government departments and provincial governments and to prevent
price fluctuations through the Spring Festival, which is a month
away.
</P>
<P>
The circular asks that government officials see to it that
supplies of food and other goods are abundant, and that price
increases are avoided.
</P>
<P>
The governments should make an effort to purchase agricultural
products, grain in particular, from farmers, and to see that grain
prices guarantee farmers' incomes.
</P>
<P>
It called for stricter price controls during the festival
period, because some business people may drive prices up during
the brisk sales period.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the random collection of various kinds of fees
must be banned, the circular said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
