<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Urgent: First Results of Singapore Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Singapore's ruling People's
Action Party (PAP) won the seat in Kam Pong Glam constituency in
the eighth general election, according to the first partial
results announced here tonight.
</P>
<P>
The winner candidate collected 13,446 votes against the
candidate of the Democratic Progress Party with 4,598 votes. There
were 604 rejected ballots.
</P>
<P>
This is the PAP's 48 seat in the 83-member Parliament because
it had already secured 47 seats on the nomination day on December
23, 1996 as other parties failed to field enough candidates in
nine of the 24 constituencies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
