<HEADLINE> 12 killed in Bomb Explosion in Damascus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, January 2 (Xinhua) -- A total of 12 people were killed
when a bomb exploded aboard a bus in the Syrian capital of
Damascus, reports reaching here from Damascus said today.
</P>
<P>
The reports, citing informed sources, said that dozens of
people were also wounded in the explosion, which occurred in the
New Year's Eve near the Baramkeh bus station in the city's
center. The bus was headed for the northern city of Aleppo.
</P>
<P>
The Syrian government, however, has yet to issue any report on
the blast.
</P>
<P>
At least 40 people were hospitalized after the explosion,
according to the reports. No one has claimed responsibility for
the blast.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian Middle East News Agency, meanwhile, said that two
explosions took place in Damascus and the coastal town of Tartus
Wednesday afternoon, killing and wounding tens of people.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that that one of the blasts occurred when an
explosive charge went off in a bus while it was getting out of the
terminal in the capital's downtown, consequently, 40 people were
killed and tens of others wounded.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that the other explosion took place at the same
time in Tartus in the west part of the country. The security
authorities rushed to the spot of the blast in downtown of the
capital and cordoned off the area to facilitate rescue operation.
</P>
<P>
The wounded were rushed to hospitals for emergency treatment.
</P>
<P>
The blasts followed a series of attacks on Syrian interests in
Lebanon. In the last two weeks, bombings aimed at Syrians in
Lebanon killed one person and wounded seven. 
</P>
</TEXT>
