<HEADLINE> Xinhua International News Summary at 1500 GMT, January 2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE -- Polling closed for the eighth general election of
Singapore with results expected to start coming out later tonight.
</P>
<P>
As of one hour ago, 94.61 percent of Singapore's 765,332 voters
in all the contested Electoral Divisions had voted. Voting is
compulsory and secret in Singapore.
</P>
<P>
During today's voting, which lasted 12 hours from 8:00 in the
morning to 8:00 in the evening, government ministers were busy
visiting the various polling stations. Among them were Deputy
Prime Ministers Lee Hsien Loong and Tony Tan, and Home Affairs
Minister Wong Kan Seng.
</P>
<P>
SEOUL -- Maritime police today rescued all but five of the 29
crewmen of an ill-fated Thai cargo vessel which sank off the south
east coast of South Korea on Wednesday, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Rescuers from the port city of Pusan found the bodies of two of
the five missing crewmen tonight. They have yet to be identified,
the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Among the rescued were the ship's captain Pradit Sripracha, 51,
and 23 others, who were winched by helicopter from the vessel
which sank just outside Pusan harbor during a storm on New Year's
Day.
</P>
<P>
Police were continuing their search for the remaining crewmen,
but their rescue operations were hampered by rough and icy seas.
</P>
<P>
The 6,677-ton Thai vessel hit a reef in heavy seas off Yong
Island just outside Pusan Harbor Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister Binyamin Netanyahu and
Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat is expected to meet today, but
they may not sign the Hebron deal, Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
