<HEADLINE> East China's Digital Mobile Phone Network Expanding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, January 2 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province has
increased its digital mobile phone coverage to include cities
above the county level, increasing the network's handling capacity
to 210,000 lines.
</P>
<P>
The province finished its first phase of construction of the
network in March 1996, providing services to 16 regions as well as
all counties within the administration of Bengbu, Fuyang, and the
provincial capital of Hefei.
</P>
<P>
The second phase of construction, which was begun in July 1996,
helped the province reach its goal of providing the service to all
cities above the county level by the end of 1996.
</P>
<P>
When its second phase of construction is completed by March
this year, the digital mobile communication service is expected to
reach many towns and main lines of communication.
</P>
<P>
The province now has analog and mobile phone networks, giving a
push to local telecommunications development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
