<HEADLINE> Nanning Using HK Funds For Infrastructure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Using the Built, Operate, and
Transfer method, Nanning, capital of south China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region, has gotten funds from Hong kong to back its
infrastructure construction.
</P>
<P>
A signing ceremony for the "Road Bridge" project of the Nanning
High-tech Development and Investment Company and Hong Kong's
Zhonghai Infrastructure Investment Co. Ltd., was held in Nanning,
with Hou Jie, the minister of construction, and Cheng Kejie,
chairman of the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Regional People's
Government, attending.
</P>
<P>
The Nanning city government is giving rights to the Hong Kong
company to run toll roads on four bridges and the Xixiangtang
highway for a period of 15 years.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Company will invest 75 million US dollars in the
construction on Shajing Avenue and a ring expressway and other
infrastructure projects in Nanning. 
