<HEADLINE> Pakistan, India Not to Attack Nuclear Facilities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan and India would not
attack each other's nuclear installations, a Pakistani Foreign
Office spokesman said here today.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman made the remarks at a weekly press briefing while
commenting on the exchange of lists of nuclear installations and
facilities between Pakistan and India.
</P>
<P>
Under their 1988 agreement on prohibition of attacks against
each other's nuclear installations and facilities, Pakistan and
India are required to exchange the lists on the first working day
of every year.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman termed the exchange as a confidence-building
measure between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
"These installations mean places of research for peaceful use
of nuclear power," he noted.  
