<HEADLINE> Petrol, Diesel prices Go up in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Prices of petrol and diesel went
up by between four and nine percent in Zimbabwe with effect from
January 1, barely three months after the last round of price
increases.
</P>
<P>
Industry sources today said that the highest increase is for
petrol which jumped from 0.42 U.S. Dollar to 0.46 Dollar per
litre, reflecting an increase of nine percent.
</P>
<P>
Diesel prices rose 0.15 U.S. Dollar per litre to 0.35 Dollar
while prices for other petroleum products remained fixed.
</P>
<P>
The latest price increases, which caught most motorists
unawares, had been necessitated by a sharp increase in import
duty for the products, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Most of Zimbabwe's petroleum products are imported from the
Middle East.
</P>
<P>
The increase is the fourth since April last year when prices
for petrolum products went up by between three and 20 percent.
</P>
