<HEADLINE> Electricity Available For All Villages In Fujian Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Electricity is now available for
all villages across southeast China's Fujian Province thanks to
the local governments' efforts in the last several years,
according to Chen Guoliang, head of the provincial hydroelectric
power administration.
</P>
<P>
Villagers in the very last village without power - Qiaotou
Village in Xiapu County - said goodbye to their days of kerosene
lamps and began a new age on December 28, 1996.
</P>
<P>
Over the past four years, the province spent some 80 million
yuan on installing 2,700 km of high-tension electrical lines,
bringing electricity to 575 villages in mountainous areas and
benefitting 500,000 villagers.
</P>
<P>
The province now has an aggregate electrical generating
capacity of 2.4 million kw, and more than 80 percent of the
province's counties and cities, as well as 40 percent of its
villages, have built their own medium-sized or small power
transmission stations. 
</P>
