<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Australian business predicted a
gloomy employment situation in the new year, with a survey
released today showing that the number of full-time jobs is
expected to fall in the first three months of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Almost 30 percent of businesses expected a drop in the number
of full-time employees in the first quarter of the year,
according to the survey conducted by the Australian Bureau of
Statistics.
</P>
<P>
