during the first quarter, the biggest drop since March 1994.
However, 18 percent of those polled expected the number of
full-time jobs to increase.
</P>
<P>
According to the survey, businesses are also pessimistic about
profits in the first three months, which are expected to decline
by 2.9 percent with medium-sized businesses bracing themselves for
a 14-percent drop.  
