<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Polling closed for the eighth
general election of Singapore with results expected to start
coming out later tonight.
</P>
<P>
As of one hour ago, 94.61 percent of Singapore's 765,332 voters
in all the contested Electoral Divisions had voted. Voting is
compulsory and secret in Singapore.
</P>
<P>
During today's voting, which lasted 12 hours from 8:00 in the
morning to 8:00 in the evening, government ministers were busy
visiting the various polling stations. Among them were Deputy
Prime Ministers Lee Hsien Loong and Tony Tan, and Home Affairs
Minister Wong Kan Seng.
</P>
<P>
Tony Tan visited Bukit Gombak and said the election had seen a
good campaign. Wong visited Jalan Besar and Potong Pasir
constituencies.
</P>
<P>
