(GRC), voters started to queue from as early as 7:00 in the
morning. Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong and Deputy Prime Minister
Lee Hsien Loong, together with the candidates of the ruling
People's Action Party (PAP), were spotted at various polling
centers in the Cheng San GRC.
</P>
<P>
Goh Chok Tong said he would probably take about two weeks to
form the cabinet after the election.
</P>
<P>
The PAP was returned to power ten days ago on the Nomination
Day when the PAP won walkovers in nine GRCs, which gave the PAP
candidates 47 of the total 83 parliament seats without election
battles.
</P>
<P>
Only 765,332, or 40.69 percent of the country's total eligible
voters, were supposed to cast their votes in the contested
constituencies. The voting will decide the other 36 seats of the
parliament.  
