<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two Hydro-Electric Power Stations For Yangtze River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Yichang, January 2 (Xinhua) -- China has decided to build two
more large hydro-electric power plants on the upper reaches of the
Yangtze River, the China Yangtze River Three Gorges Project
Development Corporation announced today.
</P>
<P>
Funds for the Xiluodu and Xiangjiaba plants will mainly come
from income from the Three Gorges Project, the world's largest,
which is taking place on the middle reaches of the river. It will
have a total installed capacity of 182 million kw upon completion.
</P>
<P>
The Xiluodu Station will be located at a point where Sichuan
and Yunnan provinces meet, on the lower reaches of the Jinsha
River, one of the Yangtze's tributaries. It has a designed
generating capacity of 14 million kilowatts, and 62.1 billion
kilowatt-hours annually.
</P>
<P>
The Xiangjiaba Station will have a generating capacity of six
million kilowatts, and 30.4 billion kilowatt-hours of power
annually, and it will also be situated on the lower reaches of the
Jinsha River.
</P>
<P>
Potential hydro-power from the Yangtze River valley is
estimated at 200 million kilowatts.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
