<HEADLINE> Initial Progress in South Chinese Economic Development Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 2 (Xinhua) -- The Nansha Economic
Development Zone in China's Guangdong Province is playing a big
role in regional development after only three years of existence.
</P>
<P>
The zone has approved 154 overseas-funded projects which have
attracted a combined contractual investment of 1.9 billion US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
About a third of these have been completed and 37 are under
construction. The majority of new projects are industrial
companies with high added-value products.
</P>
<P>
Thirty projects have used an investment of more than 10 million
US dollars each.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, the zone's industrial output value
last year doubled the previous year's figure, exceeding one
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The total amount of investment in infrastructure at the Nansha
zone was 2.3 billion yuan, 1.5 billion yuan of which was provided
by Henry Fok Ying Tung of Hong Kong. The funds have been used for
a 40-km-long highway, two deep-water wharves, and a highway
bridge.  
</P>
