<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Do Muoi, general secretary of the
Communist Party of Vietnam, has warned of corruption within the
rank of the Communist Party that weakens the popular confidence in
it, the local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing an internal security conference here, the party
leader sharply criticized violations of party discipline, moral
degeneration and public property embezzlement, saying these
activities have eroded the people's confidence in the party and
have produced gaps for the enemy to abuse in order to oppose
Vietnam's revolution.
</P>
<P>
Do Muoi called for efforts to ensure Vietnam's internal
security by strengthening and purifying party organizations, and
training party members for both ethical and professional
qualifications.
</P>
