<HEADLINE> Survey Depicts Bright Picture for HK's Banking Sector in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 2 (Xinhua) -- The latest issue of the Hong
Kong and Macao Economic Quarterly depicted a bright picture for
Hong Kong's banking sector in 1997.
</P>
<P>
A survey carried in the Quarterly, which is published by the
Bank of China Group, said that the return of Hong Kong to China
this year will generate a better operating environment for Hong
Kong's banking sector.
</P>
<P>
It predicts the growth of banking business to remain stable and
the sector to pass through the handover year smoothly despite the
existence of some unfavorable factors.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong dollar deposits is expected to grow in 1997, the GDP
will be higher than last year and more funds from foreign
countries will flow into Hong Kong after the clearing of
uncertainties regarding the handover, according to the survey.
</P>
<P>
It forecasts that loans for use in Hong Kong and overseas are
expected to grow faster in 1997. A stronger demand of loans will
be found in building and construction lending, residential
mortgage lending, consumer credit, trade financing, and financing
for mainland's and neighboring countries' infrastructure projects.
</P>
<P>
The profitability of the banking sector should be able to reach
a new height in the handover year, it said.
</P>
<P>
In 1996 Hong Kong's banking sector experienced a steady growth
against the background of an overall economic upturn.  
</P>
</TEXT>
