<HEADLINE> Innovative Personal Banking Services Launched in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Standard Chartered Bank, one
of the note-issuers in Hong Kong, launched a package of new
personal banking services today to which its customers can get
access just by dialing a telephone number.
</P>
<P>
The range of services, called Excel Banking, aims to provide
customers with reminder messages on stocks, securities, unit
trusts, foreign exchange and property market. Customers can also
overdraw their accounts through mobile phones and pagers and
arrange gift checks and demand draft and traveler's checks on a
telephone line.
</P>
<P>
Standard Chartered is the first bank in Hong Kong to offer the
package of services to integrate telecommunications technology
with customers' demand, according to Doreen Chan, head of the
Personal Banking Department. "Excel Banking provides financial
services at any time and in any place just at the fingertips of
customers," she added.
</P>
<P>
Targeted customers are professionals, managers and executives,
aged between 30 and 45, who maintain a combined quarterly average
daily balance of 150,000 HK dollars (19,000 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
"They opt for time-saving banking convenience, look for
investment opportunities and prefer to make their own decisions,"
said Chan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
