<DOCNO> XIE19970102.0088 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gansu Economy Going Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Gansu Province
witnessed booming economic development in 1996, generating more
than 67.3 billion yuan in GDP, up nearly 11 percent over the
previous year.
</P>
<P>
The province invested 23 billion yuan in fixed assets in 1996,
a rise of 18.2 percent over 1995, with spendings on agriculture
going up by a large margin.
</P>
<P>
Also in 1996, the provincial financial organizations added
nearly 1.2 billion yuan of loans for agriculture, with
expenditures on the sector's production and comprehensive
development rising 6.2 percent and 29.5 percent over 1995.
</P>
<P>
The province scored 32.5 billion yuan in agricultural output
value in 1996, with grain output topping eight billion kg and
yield per mu hitting a record high, and planted more than 165,000
hectares of trees.
</P>
<P>
Local township enterprises generated more than 57.6 billion yuan
in output value in 1996, up 41 percent over 1995. And per capita
annual net income of local farmers witnessed a record 216 yuan of
growth to surpass 1,100 yuan.
</P>
<P>
The deepening of enterprises' reforms led to stable growth in
local industrial production. More than 950 industrial
enterprises carried out a series of reforms in organizational
restructuring, rearranging more than two billion yuan of capital
and assets and providing jobs for 72,000 people.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-four local enterprises were approved as experimental
sites for the modern enterprise system, which is expected to
enliven them.
</P>
<P>
Local industrial enterprises at or above the township level
generated more than 65 billion yuan in output value in 1996, up
seven percent over 1995.
</P>
<P>
The province got more than 6.8 billion in revenues in the first
11 months of 1996, up 14.3 percent over the same period of the
previous year, with expenditures rising 10.5 percent to exceed 6.5
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
By November 1996, the province reported nearly 78 billion yuan
in bank savings, over 15 billion yuan more than at the beginning
of the year, with outstanding loans rising more than 10 billion
yuan to reach nearly 72 billion yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
