<HEADLINE> Chinese City Looking Into Social Security Fund Management </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hefei, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Tongling city, a major copper
production base in east China, is looking for ways to raise funds
for social security.
</P>
<P>
According to a city plan, a social security fund management
center has been set up, as an independent decision-maker, with
legal responsibility for the funds.
</P>
<P>
The center has been given the power to make up short-, medium-,
and long-term fund-management plans and to collect funds from
local enterprises under the city's social security program.
</P>
<P>
The center will try to increase the value of the funds through
various ways such as purchasing state and other bonds and
financing local firms. 
</P>
