<HEADLINE> Mayor: Beijing to Better Utilize Foreign Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Beijing should continue its
reform and opening-up drive, enlarge foreign trade and better
utilize overseas capital, the city's acting mayor Jia Qinglin said
at a recent municipal economic conference.
</P>
<P>
Jia pointed out that the city should place more emphasis on
quality rather than quantity when using overseas capital, and
should attract overseas investment by improving the investment
environment instead of mainly relying on preferential taxation.
</P>
<P>
According to Jia, the city used 2.25 billion U.S. dollars of
overseas investment in 1996, a rise of 14.2 percent over the
previous year.
</P>
<P>
The acting mayor stressed that the city should focus on
infrastructure projects that can reflect the city's role as an
international metropolis, projects that help improve shabby
residential buildings, and high-tech managerial programs.
</P>
<P>
Jia said that the city plans to create more laws and
regulations concerning overseas investment, adding that complaint
centers and telephone hotlines will be set up in the city to
better protect the legitimate rights of both foreign and Chinese
enterprises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
