<HEADLINE> HK Stock Market Sees 48 New Listings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 2 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong stock market
enjoyed a bumper year in 1996 for new listings with 48 new stocks
coming in, up from the 26 registered in 1995, according to today's
South China Morning Post.
</P>
<P>
Of the 48 new listings, 44 are fully-fledged initial public
offerings (IPO) while four of them have come to the market by way
of introduction.
</P>
<P>
The report said that many analysts predict the total number of
new listings in 1997 may surpass the high of 53 listed in 1994,
and the greatest potential relies on mainland-related companies.
</P>
<P>
Analysts believe that new listings will perform even better
this year as a spate of China shares are likely to keep the IPO
fervor on the boil.
</P>
<P>
Among the 44 IPOs, the close of the year saw 28 trading above
their issue price while 16 trading below, according to the report.
</P>
</TEXT>
