<HEADLINE> Bangladeshis to Get Compensation for Gulf War </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of Bangladeshis who
returned from Iraq and Kuwait due to the Gulf War in 1990 will
soon get a package of compensation of 50 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to sources at the Ministry of Labor and Manpower
today, the decision was made by the Governing Council of the U.N.
Commission for Compensation (UNCC) at its recent meeting.
</P>
<P>
The UNCC has decided to release 142 million dollars for 56,000
successful claimants in 17 countries during the first quarter of
this year and of the total initial allocation, Bangladesh will
receive about 50 million dollars for more than 20,000 successful
claimants, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that approximately 70,000 Bangladeshi wage
earners had to return home in the wake of the Gulf War. Many of
them suffered huge financial losses by losing their jobs and
property.  
</P>
</TEXT>
