<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Cement Output Hits Record in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's cement output in 1996
hit a record high of 5.3 million tonnes, 300,000 over last year,
Vietnam Cement Corporation (VCC) said here today.
</P>
<P>
The national VCC, fulfilling its yearly plan on december 27,
four days ahead of schedule, produced 1.72 million tonnes
averaging 600,000 tonnes per month.
</P>
<P>
The Hoang Thach Cement Company, which topped the list of the
VCC's affiliates, produced a total of 1.74 million tonnes,
accounting for one-third of its total.
</P>
<P>
Cement prices in Vietnam were stable last year largely due to
VCC's efforts to increase production, reduce cost and improve
sales, with its retail network of 1,420 shops and agents working
across the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
