<HEADLINE> Hainan Outlines Key Aspects for Overseas Investment Utilization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Hainan, China's largest special
economic zone, will absorb a huge amount of overseas investment
this year to develop high and new technology, upgrade existing
state-owned industrial firms and boost agricultural growth.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investment will be introduced to conduct technological
transformation and build a modern enterprise system at local
state-owned enterprises, according to a provincial government
official.
</P>
<P>
Those investing in pillar industries, high-tech programs and
key projects will enjoy preferential treatment granted by
governments at various levels.
</P>
<P>
The State Planning Commission has approved construction of the
Meilan International Airport at Hainan's capital city of Haikou,
the Shiji (Century) bridge, which will be built at a cost of 50
million US dollars, and a natural gas pipeline which will involve
an investment of 30 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Other industrial and infrastructure projects scheduled include
a sewage disposal undertaking, which will use 21.8 million German
marks in loans, a waterworks system involving 7.3 million German
marks loan by the German Government, and a zinc-coated sheet plant
funded by 15 million US dollars in loans granted by the Republic
of Korea.  
</P>
</TEXT>
