<HEADLINE> Malaysia, Finland to Cooperate More on Fire Fighting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia and Finland signed
a Memorandum of Understanding (MOU) here today on expanding their
cooperation in fire-fighting services.
</P>
<P>
The MOU, signed by Malaysian Housing and Local Government
Minister Ting Chew Peh and Finnish Home Minister Jan-Erik Enestam
who arrived here yesterday, covers training facilities, exchange
of expertise and information, research and other programs in
fire-fighting services, Ting told reporters after the signing.
</P>
<P>
Another MOU was signed between Malaysia's private Pantas
Fabristeel Company Limited and Finland's Carrus Oy Group of
Companies on cooperation in building fire-rescue vehicles for the
local and Asia-Pacific markets.
</P>
<P>
Ting said Finland has also expressed interest in sharing with
Malaysia its expertise and advanced technology in toxic waste
management and disposal as well as in cooperation with the
Malaysian private sector in low-cost house construction.  
</P>
</TEXT>
