<HEADLINE> Russian Serviceman Killed in Tajikistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 2 (Xinhua) -- A Russian soldier was shot dead
in Tajikistan's capital of Dushanbe overnight Wednesday, according
to reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
The body of Alexander Goncharov, a serviceman of Russia's 201st
Motorized Infantry Division, was found in Dushanbe's southern
district, with a pistol bullet in the head, A Russian military
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
It was the third such attack in a week on the Russian Division
deployed in Dushanbe.
</P>
<P>
Dozens of Russian servicemen have been reportedly killed and
injured in Tajikistan, where they carry out peacekeeping mission
and guard the border with Afghanistan. 
