<HEADLINE> New Money-Pooling Method In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Commercial paper made its
debut in south China's Shenzhen Special Economic Zone recently,
raising 220 million yuan for nine local cash-short enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The companies issued the five-month commercial paper in the
local money market to raise funds at an annual interest rate of
11.0074 percent, a move that was well received by local financial
institutions and enterprises.
</P>
<P>
"The new fund-pooling method will do a lot of good for Chinese
enterprises, given its ability to help improve their debt
structure and liquidity of operational capital," said one
financial expert, who noted that the new capital-raising option
will also ease the burden on banks.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen has developed the financial business in inter-bank
lending, the buy-back of bonds, and in discounting acceptance
bills in its money market, which is expected to raise a total of
more than 20 billion yuan this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
