<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Aims to Produce 30 Billion cu m of Natural Gas Annually </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 2 (Xinhua) -- China plans to double its annual
natural gas production capacity to 30 billion cu m by the year
2005, as one of its important strategies for developing energy
resources.
</P>
<P>
According to a senior official with the China National
Petroleum Corp. (CNPC), China is expected to verify additional
onshore gas reserves of one trillion cu m by the end of the
century, with the accumulative total hitting two trillion cu m.
</P>
<P>
By then, the country's gas production capacity will be
increased by another 10 billion cu m, with the total topping 25
billion cu m.
</P>
<P>
The CNPC source said that through further exploration, major
breakthroughs are forecast in the expansion of proven gas reserves
and production capacity in the Shaanxi-Gansu-Ningxia region, the
Tarim Basin and Sichuan Province. And the annual gas output will
reach 30 billion cu m by the year 2005.
</P>
<P>
The CNPC official noted that enormous potential exists for the
country's gas production. Following years of vigorous development,
three large-scale gas production areas have taken shape in the
country.
</P>
<P>
In the central part of the Shaanxi-Gansu-Ningxia region, total
gas reserves of 230 billion cu m have been verified. Total gas
reserves of 200 billion cu m have been proven in the eastern part
of Sichuan. In the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, total gas
reserves of 160 billion cu m have been verified, in addition to
the discovery of a group of new gas-bearing structures.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, in the Sebei area of northwest China's Qinghai
Province, a large gas field with proven reserves of 50 billion cu
m has been found.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the domestic gas exploration, active efforts are
being made to utilize gas resources of neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
In central Asia, China has joined an international gas
exploration project which will involve the construction of a
long-distance gas pipeline running through China and the Korean
Peninsula to Japan, providing China with a gas supply of 25
billion cu m a year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a joint venture with Russia for gas exploration in
eastern Siberia will pipe to China 25 billion cu m of gas annually.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970102.0124 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Government to Help Save Loss-Making NBC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, January 2 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzanian government
has dispatched an expert team to do an in-depth study on how to
turn the loss-making National Bank of Commerce (NBC) into a
viable bank.
</P>
<P>
The Financial Ministry said in a statement on Wednesday that
the team will draft details on how to improve NBC's banking
services, especially in the field of foreign trade, and issuing
loans to individuals, to medium or large-sized enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The NBC, founded in 1967, had about 18.5 million U.S. dollars
of capitals, 85.6 million dollars of reserves and 627.5 million
dollars of deposits around the beginning of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Although the NBC has cut its operational costs and closed down
some of its branches around the eastern African country, it is
still in the red as many of its loans failed to be honored.
</P>
<P>
The government will supervise all the preparations for the
four-or-five-year NBC restructuring program, which will be
carefully implemented with a view to putting the national
interests first, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
Under the program, the current NBC stuff will retain to carry
out the recovering plan, many of them involved in the earlier
streamlining and retrenchment of the NBC after the Banking and
Financial Institutions Act took effect in 1991.
</P>
<P>
The government plans to strengthen the NBC, not to weaken or
kill it, the statement reiterated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
