<HEADLINE> Biggest Redemption Case For Chinese Insurance Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Zhang Xi, a poor farmer's son
from suburban Shanghai who suffers from a liver disease, has
received a medical insurance compensation claim of nearly 200,000
yuan from the local branch of the People's Life Insurance Company
of China.
</P>
<P>
This is the largest sum of insurance redemption ever paid by a
Chinese life insurance company in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The 14-year-old boy was diagnosed with the ailment last
April. Doctors said he would not survive if his liver was not
removed immediately.
</P>
<P>
Zhang's parents could not afford the surgery. Fortunately, he
had paid 15 yuan to buy the PICC policy that covered all expenses
for medical treatment.
</P>
<P>
About 95 percent of the students in the city's primary and
middle schools have bought the medical insurance policy. The
Shanghai branch of PICC Life has paid out about 100 million yuan
in redemption fees over the past five years.  
</P>
