<HEADLINE> Foreign Companies Encouraged to Invest in West Caohejing Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 2 (Xinhua) -- The western region of the
Caohejing Hi-tech Development Zone in Shanghai has been opened and
zone officials are welcoming business people to invest in the
district.
</P>
<P>
One of the national-level high-tech development zones, the area
covers 5.98 square kilometers, and is home to 500 Chinese and
foreign high-tech enterprises. The zone's sales income averages
three billion yuan per square kilometer.
</P>
<P>
The 1.89-square-kilometer west district features roads, power,
water and telephone facilities, and is a suitable site for
establishing enterprises.
</P>
<P>
