<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indian Export Up by 7.8 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 2 (Xinhua) -- For the first time in the last
few years India's exports fell by 3.81 percent to 2481.13 million
US dollars in November bringing down the export growth rate to
7.81 percent during April-November 1996, official sources said
here today.
</P>
<P>
The value of exports during the above-mentioned period stood at
21,390.53 million dollars while total imports increased by 4.66
percent to 24,216.96 million US dollars. The trade deficit in the
first eight months of the current financial year ( April
1,1996-March 31,1997) stood at 2,826.43 million US dollars
compared to 3,296.65 million last year.
</P>
<P>
Value of oil imports stood at 6,011.34 million US dollars, up
by 41.44 percent over the corresponding period last year. Non-oil
imports during April-November, however, were estimated at 1,805.62
million US dollars, 3.61 percent lower than the level of such
imports in the same period in 1995.  
</P>
</TEXT>
