<HEADLINE> China Has 530 Listed Companies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Last year, 207 Chinese companies
were listed on the country's two stock markets, lifting the total
to 530, up from 323 in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The Shenzhen Stock Exchange's 293 listed firms outnumbered the
those on the Shanghai Exchange which totaled 237 at year's end.
</P>
<P>
Shares listed in Shenzhen are valued at 18.659 billion yuan,
compared with the 15.876 billion yuan from the Shanghai market.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover in the Chinese stock market hit 4.161
trillion yuan last year, more than six times the amount for 1995.
</P>
<P>
The number of stock investors rose by more than eight million,
reaching 20 million during the past year. 
</P>
