<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy to Reduce Military Service Term </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Italian joint chiefs are working on
a ministerial decree to officially reduce its military
conscription term from one year to 10 months, defense officials
say.
</P>
<P>
The measure, included in the 1997 budget approved by Parliament
last month, is the first step of Defense Minister Beniamino
Andreatta's reform plan called "The New Model of Defense."
</P>
<P>
The next step was expected to be the creation of a national
service system, both civil and military, in which participants
could choose from a variety of ways to serve their country,
sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
