<HEADLINE> Roundup:  China Becoming Active Force in Multilateral </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 2 (Xinhua) -- China's active involvement in
international multilateral cooperation in 1996 proves the nation
has become a dynamic force in global diplomacy.
</P>
<P>
And the country has attained greater international influence as
a result of Chinese leaders' participation in multilateral
diplomatic activities.
</P>
<P>
At the Fourth Informal Leadership Meeting of the Asian-Pacific
Economic Cooperation (APEC), Chinese President Jiang Zemin
explained the guiding principle that equal attention should be
paid to regional economic and technological cooperation, and to
the liberalization of investment.
</P>
<P>
During the First Asia-Europe Meeting, Premier Li Peng expressed
China's view on a new partnership between Asia and Europe. At the
World Food Summit, he outlined the issue of the world's food
supply, and explained the country's agricultural policy.
</P>
<P>
A delegation of government officials led by Chinese
Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen also attended the
51st UN General Assembly.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, following the UN Fourth World Conference on Women the
previous fall, China successfully hosted a series of specialized
and comprehensive international conferences.
</P>
<P>
The meetings turned Beijing into an international center for
communication, where tens of thousands of political dignities,
scholars and well-known public figures from all over the world
exchanged ideas and information.
</P>
<P>
At the first meeting of the 21st Century Forum and 96th
Inter-Parliamentary Conference, common understandings on major
international and regional issues were reached through in-depth
discussions. The outcome of both meetings greatly contributed to
international cooperation based on equality, and world peace and
development.
</P>
<P>
And during these meetings, the talks between Chinese leaders
and many government and parliament officials of other countries
gave strong impetus to the improvement and development of
bilateral ties between China and other countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
