<HEADLINE> Henman Advances in Qatar Tennis Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT, January 1 (Xinhua) -- British tennis number one Tim
Henman advanced into the quarter-finals with a 6-3, 6-2 victory
over Tamer El Sawy of Egypt at the Qatar Open tennis tournament in
Doha on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Henman, who beat El Sawy in their Davis Cup tie last year,
easily disposed of the 149th ranked Egyptian taking the first set
in only 31 minutes. El Sawy had put out the third seed Jan
Siemerink of the Netherlands in the first round.
</P>
<P>
The 22-year-old Henman, who failed to make an ATP final last
year despite qualifying for six semi-finals but saw his ranking
rise to 29 in the world from 99, will play experienced Swede
Magnus Gustafsson in the quarter-finals. Gustafsson, seeded
fifth, beat rising Czech star Dominik Hrbaty in three sets.
</P>
<P>
Morocco's Hicham Arazi celebrated a 2-6, 7-5, 7-5 win over
Patrick McEnroe, who was playing his first match on the circuit
since suffering a shoulder injury in March 1996.
</P>
<P>
Arazi will face Gustafsson's hardhitting compatriot Magnus
Larsson who disposed of another Swede Patrik Fredriksson 6-4, 7-6
(7/4). 
</P>
</TEXT>
