<HEADLINE> Teenager Peterka Wins New Year Ski Jumping Event </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Slovenian teenager Primoz Peterka
captured a convincing New Year victory on Wednesday in a World Cup
ski jumping in Garmisch-Partenkirchen, Germany.
</P>
<P>
Peterka, 17, flied 117.5 and 118.0 meters in two jumps to put
him well clear of the day's next best distance of 115.5 meters,
achieved by Germany's Dieter Thoma and Takanobu Okabe of Japan.
</P>
<P>
The jumps gave him a total of 241.9 points. Austria's World Cup
champion Andreas Goldberger, had two 114.0 meters leaps to earn
228.9 points, and Okabe came third with 226.7.
</P>
<P>
Peterka's win put him on 492 points in the World Cup standings
after eight events, ahead of Goldberger on 432 and Norway's
Kristian Brenden on 427. 
</P>
</TEXT>
