<HEADLINE> Croatia Crashed in Hopman Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Reigning champions Croatia
crashed to the unseeded United States in the Hopman Cup tennis
mixed team tournament in Perth on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In the biggest upset so far in the eight-nation contest,
Croatia's Goran Ivanisevic and Iva Majoli were toppled by United
States pair Justin Gimelstob and Chanda Rubin.
</P>
<P>
The United States won 2-1, clinching the tie when Gimelstob and
Rubin teamed up to beat the Croatians in a two-hour, three-set
mixed doubles thriller.
</P>
<P>
The Americans won the doubles 6-3, 3-6, 7-6 (9/7).
</P>
<P>
Rubin won the women's singles and Ivanisevic made it all-square
when he beat Gimelstob, who flew in as a last minute replacement
for Richey Reneberg when Rneberg's wife had their first child, in
the men's singles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
