<HEADLINE> Gansu's Telephone Switching Capacity Exceeds One Million Lines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Gansu
province increased its telephone switching capacity to one million
lines on December 26, by extending the program-controlled
telephone switching system to all its counties.
</P>
<P>
The rapid telecom growth in the landlocked province should be
attributed to the local governments' heavy investment and the
preferential policies given to the industry, according to the
"People's Posts and Telecommunications News."
</P>
<P>
Last year, the province spent 1.3 billion yuan on the
telecommunications projects, expanding the digital transmission
services to 78.6 percent of its cities.
</P>
<P>
At present, the services of packet exchange and DDN (digital
and data network) are available in most of the counties, and the
downtown area of Lanzhou, the provincial capital, is accessible to
the GSM (global service for mobile communication) service.
</P>
<P>
During the past few years, the province built five local
telephone networks, 27,000 long-distance phone lines and three
optical cable trunks now connect Lanzhou with Beijing and other
neighboring provincial capitals.
</P>
<P>
Acting Governor Sun Ying said that telecommunications is the
most rapidly developing industry in the economically
underdeveloped province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
