<HEADLINE> Foreign Experts Helping Northwest Chinese Industries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, January 2 (Xinhua) -- The Bayi Sugar Refinery in
Shihezi City, in the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, increased
the number of premier products from 22 percent of its total to
over 90 percent within one month of getting help from a German
expert.
</P>
<P>
The introduction of foreign expertise has brought new vitality
to the refinery, the largest and oldest of its kind in China's
northwest. The company had been having a number of difficulties
for quite a long time.
</P>
<P>
According to local officials, experts from abroad have been
involved in a number of local industries such as road-building,
oil exploration, metallurgy, and leather goods, helping bring to
Xinjiang an additional two billion yuan in increased production
value and 25 million US dollars from exports.
</P>
<P>
Since the late '70s, over 4,500 foreign experts from the United
States, Canada, Australia, Germany, Italy, and the Commonwealth of
Independent States (CIS) have worked in the autonomous region.
</P>
</TEXT>
