<HEADLINE> China's Largest Frequency Converter Production Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, January 2 (Xinhua) -- China's largest frequency
converter production center will be built in this capital of
Sichuan Province, in a move to enhance the competitiveness of
domestically-manufactured products.
</P>
<P>
The center will manufacture 300,000 frequency changers annually
when completed around the year 2000. It will be built by the
Chengdu-based Jialing Electric Manufacturing Company.
</P>
<P>
Frequency changers are widely used in electrical applicances
like fans, and in diesel locomotives and subway cars where speeds
have to be regulated by an electric motor.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, China used one billion yuan worth of the items and
demand is rising at an annual rate of 20 percent.
</P>
<P>
China has 50 frequency converter manufacturers, but their
output accounts for only three percent of the country's market,
due to the low level of technology.
</P>
<P>
The production center will use advanced technology and is
expected to produce hi-tech frequency changers to improve the
technical standards of Chinese products.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
