<HEADLINE> Eastern Province Has More Cellular Phone Users </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, January 2 (Xinhua) -- The number of cellular phone
subscribers in east China's Jiangsu Province totaled 450,000 by
the end of 1996, an increase of 220,000 over the 1995 figure.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu now ranks third, following Guangdong and Zhejiang
provinces, in terms of its number of mobile phone users, according
to official statistics.
</P>
<P>
The province started the cellular phone service in 1992 and has
invested nearly five billion yuan in building up three major
mobile phone networks that cover all cities and counties. These
systems are on-line with the national webs and a number of
overseas networks.
</P>
<P>
To date, the province's cellular networks have 46 cellular
exchanges, 1,600 basic stations and over 50,000 channels, and are
capable of serving more than one million users. 
</P>
