<HEADLINE> China to Expand Insurance Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 2 (Xinhua) -- China will open its domestic
insurance market wide to overseas companies and compete in the
world insurance market this year, according to an official with
the country's central bank.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a symposium on insurance held here recently Yu Hua,
an official with the central bank, the People's Bank of China,
says that earnings from China's insurance business amounted to
36.87 billion yuan in the first half of 1996, up 32 percent from
the same period in 1995.
</P>
<P>
But there is great potential and China's insurance business is
still in a "start-up period."
</P>
<P>
China currently has 21 insurance companies dealing in life and
property insurance in China, seven of which are foreign-funded.
</P>
<P>
This does not meet the growing demand however, and much of the
insurance offered does not cover most aspects of life, she noted.
</P>
<P>
She said that China will try to perfect its laws related to
insurance, and to increase the number of insurance companies this
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
