<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ADB Cuts Lending Rates For US Dollar Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 2 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
Wednesday cut the lending rate on its US dollar loan facility from
6.82 percent to 6.79 percent per annum.
</P>
<P>
The ADB said the new lending rates will apply from January 1 to
June 30, 1997. The rate on multi-currency loans remains unchanged
at 6 percent per annum.
</P>
<P>
The interest rates on the ADB's multi-currency and US dollar
loans are adjusted on January 1 and July 1 each year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
