<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Venezuela Plans Boost To Petroleum Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, January 1 (Xinhua) -- PDVSA, Venezuela's state-owned
petroleum corporation, says it will try to enhance its abilities
to explore and refine petroleum in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The corporation predicted a 9.4 percent growth of petrochemical
products in the new year, to 4.5 million metric tons. This was on
the basis of an upsurge of foreign investment, and greater
efficiency of its plants and joint ventures.
</P>
<P>
The PDVSA said it would invest about one billion dollars to
explore ten oil fields considered to be of high risk. It hoped by
doing this to increase its proven reserves of crude oil to 68.18
million barrels, 3.9 percent more than in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
