<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Flu Hits Hard on Southern Czech Republic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Flu is hitting hard on the
southern part of the Czech Republic and running down about 2
percent of the population there, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The outbreak, brought in partly by the recent cold front
sweeping across the entire European continent, is threatening to
further spread into the country's northern part.
</P>
<P>
Last week alone saw more than 20,000 new flu cases in the
north, said the reports quoting medical authorities.
</P>
<P>
Over the past week, daylight high temperatures have been
hovering around minus 16-18 Celsius in the Czech Republic, the
lowest for the region in 27 years.
</P>
<P>
The government, fearing the flu would claim more victims after
the Christmas holiday season, has advised people to take a vaccine
injection and keep away from public places. 
</P>
</TEXT>
