<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Telecom Industry Has Assets of 25.8 Billion Yuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 2 (Xinhua) -- China's telecommunications
sector now has 25.8 billion yuan of assets and 406 manufacturing
plants, ranking among the world's emerging telecom powers.
</P>
<P>
Of the 406 plants, 188 are state-owned and 51 are
foreign-funded, altogether employing 94,000 people, according to a
survey conducted by the Ministry of Posts and Telecommunications .
</P>
<P>
In 1995, the telecom industry scored a turnover of 17 billion
yuan, and made 1.76 billion yuan in profits.
</P>
<P>
These figures are computed through the year-long nationwide
survey.
</P>
<P>
Yang Xianzu, vice minister of Posts and Telecommunications,
said that the industry's product range and manufacturing scale are
growing fast, thanks to progress achieved in the research and
development fields in the past five years.
</P>
<P>
However, Yang said, there are not enough large enterprises to
meet the demand of an economy of scale. Therefore, the ministry
will place more emphasis on building big conglomerates and
enterprise groups in the coming years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
