<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Indian Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 2 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Indian newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
The Hindustan Times
</P>
<P>
-- The Congress Working Committee, the highest policy-making
body of the party, Wednesday night cleared the decks for Congress
President Sitaram Kesri to take over as the "consensus" leader of
the Congress Parliamentary Party on January 3.
</P>
<P>
The Times of India
</P>
<P>
-- People in New Delhi went without electricity on the New
Year's day as the Dadri power station tripped early Wednesday
morning.
</P>
<P>
The Statesman
</P>
<P>
-- A train carrying passengers of the Brahmaputra Mail, damaged
in the bomb blast in lower Assam state's Kokrajhar district on
Monday, is expected to reach the old Delhi Railway Station
Thursday morning.
</P>
<P>
The Economic Times
</P>
<P>
-- The Bombay Stock Exchange market ushered in the new year
with a robust 175-point jump amid hectic buying activity from
punters.  
</P>
