<HEADLINE> Switzerland Hands Over OSCE Chairmanship to Denmark </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Switzerland today handed over its
chairmanship of the Organization for Security and Cooperation in
Europe (OSCE) to Denmark, according to local press reports.
</P>
<P>
Switzerland, Denmark and Poland, next Chairman-in-Office, form
the OSCE troika in 1997. 
</P>
