<HEADLINE> Ugandan President Calls for Commodity Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri
Museveni today called for the development of commodity production in
his new year address.
</P>
<P>
Commodity production have revitalised in some extent the
economy of Uganda, he said.
</P>
<P>
Yoweri Museveni released his speach to the nation from his home at
Rwakitura, southwestern Uganda, Radio Uganda reported today.
</P>
<P>
He appealed people to produce enough food to support their family
members and keep a surplus for sale, and called on all local leaders
to increase productivity in their areas.
</P>
<P>
He told the nation that the inflation rate remained steady at
5.3 percent, industrial production increased by 17.3 percent in
the 1995-96 financial year, and the revenue collection is
expected to be around 800 billion Uganda Shillings (some 800
million US Dollars) in the current financial year.
</P>
<P>
Uganda should diversify its export so that coffe becomes only
one of its exports, he stressed. enditem

